&nbsp;
At the parade of the Royal Guard, on June 15, there will be King Charles > who however will inspect the troops from the inside of the carriage, and not on horseback as he did last year. The princess, sick of cancer, is undergoing a precautionary chemotherapy. The Daily Mail in recent days wrote that it was spotted around the castle, along with her husband and children: a glimmer of hope> after so many conflicting news about his state of health, including the suffering of a very aggressive tumor: a tumor to ovaries operated - according to unconfirmed sources - by two Italian doctors, a world-famous luminaire and a colleague who accompanied him to London.
