AGI -&nbsp;The Council adopted a regulation imposing prohibitive tariffs on cereal products imported from Russia and Belarus. The Regulation increases duties on cereals, oilseeds and products derived from Russia and Belarus at a point such as to block imports of these products in practice. The measures concern products originating or exported directly or indirectly by the Russian Federation or the Republic of Belarus to the EU. They will not affect transit through the EU from both countries to other third countries.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Gentiloni, our duty to contribute to the result
&nbsp;
&nbsp; "Russia has made a war of aggression, I think it is our duty as Europeans to contribute to a result that demonstrates that the wars of aggression against their neighbors are in violation of international law and cannot have the best". To say so, the European Commissioner for Economic and Monetary Affairs Paolo Gentiloni today in Turin, on the increase in cereal duties.
