<br> "The defendants involved in the unofficial primary elections organized by the pro-democracy opposition in Hong Kong in July 2020 are affected by a peaceful political activity which should be legitimate in any political system that respects fundamental democratic principles. The EU is deeply concerned about the judicial process politically motivated against the 47 defenders of democracy, the prolonged preventive detention and the refusal of bail for most defendants, who undermine trust in the rule of law enshrined in the Basic Law of Hong Kong," the spokesman said.
